      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument for solely relying on solar and wind is driven by the current cost advantages and the perceived safety profile of those technologies. However, this perspective often overlooks the intermittency challenge, which requires massive, often unproven, energy storage solutions to guarantee constant power. A 100% renewable future is an aspirational goal, but nuclear energy provides a proven, dispatchable, carbon-free baseload power that accelerates the transition while storage technology catches up.",
